    "DL combined with guided local search • GAT + GLS algorithmIn 2021, Hudson et al. [66] proposed an algorithm that combines GAT with GLS for TSP.As depicted in Fig.",
    "22, this algorithm transforms a given TSP graph into a line graph (where nodes represent edges of the original graph) and employs a GAT on the line graph to compute regret value for each edge.",
    "These predicted regret values guide the search process of GLS.The model is also trained using supervised learning.",
    "The algorithm was evaluated on TSP20, TSP50, and TSP100 datasets, demonstrating superior solution quality compared to existing DL-based algorithms at the time.n n(n -1)/2However, the transformation of a TSP graph into a line graph increases the graph size from to, adding computational overhead and complexity, which is not favorable for handling large-scale TSPs.",
    "• NeuralGLS algorithmIn 2024, Sui al."
  ]
}